definition: to pass on/to spread/to transmit/to infect/to transfer/to circulate/to conduct (electricity)
to enter/to go into/to join/to become a member of/to confirm or agree with/abbr. for 入聲|入声[ru4 sheng1]
afferent nerve (transmitting in to the brain)/afferent neuron

sentences.english: The server unwinds the envelope and executes the named methods with the passed arguments.
sentences.chinese: 服務器打開信封並使用傳入參數執行指定的方法。

sentences.english: The lurgy in question was, the researchers suggest, imported from Australia.
sentences.chinese: 研究者認爲，這種疾病是從澳大利亞傳入的。

sentences.english: Almond tea was introduced by the civil court of a snack.
sentences.chinese: 杏仁茶是由宮廷傳入民間的一種風味小喫。

sentences.english: Western modern sericulture was introduced into China in the late Qing Dynasty.
sentences.chinese: 西方近代化蠶學理論和養蠶技術於晚清傳入中國。

sentences.english: Croquet first played in Hawaii at Punahou School in Honolulu.
sentences.chinese: 槌球首次傳入夏威夷火奴魯魯的帕納胡學校。

sentences.english: Think of efferent coupling as the inverse of afferent coupling.
sentences.chinese: 可以把傳出耦合看作傳入耦合的逆轉。

sentences.english: It was after Opium War that Western photography was introduced into China.
sentences.chinese: 攝影術是鴉片戰爭後由西方傳入我國的。

sentences.english: Huangshan in the Jin dynasty, when Buddhism introduced, under the peak Regulus Regulus temple was built.
sentences.chinese: 佛教在晉朝時傳入黃山，軒轅峯下曾建有軒­轅古剎。

sentences.english: The introduction of western medicine into China was closely related to the medical activities of western missionaries in China.
sentences.chinese: 西醫學的傳入與傳教士在華的醫學活動分不開。

sentences.english: You can pass any one variable to a function at most once in the argument list.
sentences.chinese: 你最多隻能把任一變量傳入參數表中一次。

sentences.english: Rome's military invasion of Great Britain, Scottish pipers introduced.
sentences.chinese: 羅馬軍隊入侵大不列顛的時候，風笛傳入蘇格蘭。

sentences.english: Incoming change sets are ones that have been delivered to the stream by other team members.
sentences.chinese: 傳入變更集是已經由其他團隊成員交付到流的變更集。

sentences.english: Afferent coupling is harder to determine and much more valuable.
sentences.chinese: 傳入耦合比較難判斷，但是更有價值。

sentences.english: Papermaking began in China and from here it spread to North Africa and Europe.
sentences.chinese: 造紙術開始於中國，隨後傳入北非和歐洲。

sentences.english: Some primary afferent neurons were presented in the nodose ganglia.
sentences.chinese: 部分初級傳入神經元位於迷走神經結狀節內。

sentences.english: Afferent coupling represents the count of how many other classes use the current class.
sentences.chinese: 傳入耦合表示有多少個其他類使用當前類。

definition: to pass on/to spread/to transmit/to infect/to transfer/to circulate/to conduct (electricity)
to rise/to spring up/to burgeon/to be aroused/to come into vogue
to come from (a place)/From: (in email header)
to differentiate/to draw a distinction/to divide into categories
